<topic id="whatisgithub">
    <title>What is GitHub?</title>
    <body>
        <p>GitHub is a code hosting platform for version control and collaboration. It lets you and others work together on projects from anywhere.</p>
        <p>This tutorial teaches you GitHub essentials like <i>repositories</i>, <i>branches</i>,
                <i>commits</i>, and <i>Pull Requests</i>. You’ll create your own Hello World
            repository and learn GitHub’s Pull Request workflow, a popular way to create and review
            code.</p>
    </body>
</topic>
